I made a mistake in the original problem definition. Try:<p><pre><code>  graphics.beginFill(0xFFFFFFFF);
  graphics.drawRect(10, 10, 100, 100);
  graphics.endFill();
</code></pre>
The extra "FF" for alpha triggers it. But change any one of the entries to FE and it's fixed again.<p>Edit(2): I just realized that this must stem from the behavior of Flash's unsigned 32-bit integers. Doubly odd since you'd think they'd mention this.
